        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2018-05-01 23:01:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2\n\nConverting the CLASSERT()s is thankfully pretty straight forward, since any errors will be caught at build time (assuming the code is not #ifdef'd out).\n\nConverting LASSERT() and LASSERTF() to BUG_ON() will be more complex, and we'll lose useful information.  I always disliked the kernel BUG_ON(), since it only prints the line number and doesn't give any opportunity like LASSERTF() to provide additional useful data like what the actual values were.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
